- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the computational complexity of determining the Hadwiger number on different classes of graphs, which is a fundamental algorithmic problem. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper deals with the problem of finding the largest complete minor in a graph, which is a geometric property of the graph. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The Hadwiger number is a concept that is used in the study of graph coloring and game theory.
